        "comment": {
            "name": "comment",
            "type": "com.atlassian.jira.issue.fields.CommentSystemField",
            "value": [
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38011",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Actually, the output is exactly as it should be. The default decorators are configured such that the label decorator has the \"tag\" option configured to create a <dt> tag wrapping it.\r\n\r\nIf you do not desire this, you can reconfigure the label decorator:\r\n{code}\r\n$form->title->getDecorator('label')->setOption('tag', null);\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=matthew",
                        "name": "matthew",
                        "displayName": "Matthew Weier O'Phinney",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-25T08:50:02.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-25T08:50:02.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38013",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Hi Matthew,\r\n\r\nthanks for your quick reply. I did not see the foreach loop in your blog post :\r\n\r\n{code}\r\nforeach ($form->getElements() as $element) {\r\n    $element->getDecorator('label')->setOption('tag', null);\r\n}\r\n{code}\r\n\r\nI'm strarting an new project and all the forms are going to be render manually. Is there an other solution to make it more trivial ? May be I could overload the label decorator... I have to check.",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-25T09:11:26.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-25T09:11:26.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38014",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "What about something like this ?\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n<?= $form->title->renderLabel('', array('tag'=> null)); ?>\r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-25T09:23:27.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-25T09:23:27.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38015",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "I just tried your code snippet but the output is steal the same :\r\n\r\n{code}\r\n<dt id=\"title-label\"><label for=\"title\" tag=\"\" class=\"required\">Title:<\/label><\/dt> \r\n{code}",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "created": "2010-01-25T09:30:55.000+0000",
                    "updated": "2010-01-25T09:30:55.000+0000"
                },
                {
                    "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/comment\/38041",
                    "author": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "In fact doing\r\n{code}\r\n$form->title->getDecorator('label')->setOption('tag', null);\r\n{code}\r\n\r\ndoesn't remove the dt but add a ' tag=\"\" ' attribute to the label element. Is it a bug ?",
                    "updateAuthor": {
                        "self": "http:\/\/fw02.zend.com\/issues\/rest\/api\/latest\/user?username=laurent+melmoux",
                        "name": "laurent melmoux",
                        "displayName": "Laurent Melmoux",
                        "active": true
                    },
